          <flip_chart-teacher-facing-content-box>
            <flip_chart-teacher-facing-paragraph>Whether you’re looking for a delicious snack or a healthy dessert, everyone loves delicious fruit salad! This recipe is a favorite, but you can change it to add a different favorite fruit if you’d like.</flip_chart-teacher-facing-paragraph>
            <flip_chart-teacher-facing-paragraph><flip_chart-bold>Ingredients:</flip_chart-bold>
              <flip_chart-br> </flip_chart-br>3 sliced bananas<flip_chart-br> </flip_chart-br> 2 cups of sliced apples<flip_chart-br> </flip_chart-br> 1  cup of sliced strawberries<flip_chart-br> </flip_chart-br> 2 cut-up mangoes</flip_chart-teacher-facing-paragraph> <flip_chart-teacher-facing-paragraph>
              <flip_chart-bold>Directions:</flip_chart-bold>
              <flip_chart-br> </flip_chart-br><flip_chart-bold>Step 1.</flip_chart-bold> Wash the fruit.<flip_chart-br> </flip_chart-br><flip_chart-bold>Step 2.</flip_chart-bold> Peel the bananas and ask an adult to help cut all the fruit.<flip_chart-br> </flip_chart-br><flip_chart-bold>Step 3.</flip_chart-bold> Use measuring cups to measure the apples and strawberries and put them in the bowl.<flip_chart-br> </flip_chart-br><flip_chart-bold>Step 4.</flip_chart-bold> Add the mangoes to the bowl.<flip_chart-br> </flip_chart-br><flip_chart-bold>Step 5.</flip_chart-bold> Mix all of the fruit together.</flip_chart-teacher-facing-paragraph><flip_chart-teacher-facing-paragraph>Serve the fruit salad. Enjoy!</flip_chart-teacher-facing-paragraph>
          </flip_chart-teacher-facing-content-box>
